anuFbPk2fETM1BjyzRRPT0Coa0qtN_Wh9b_9caV5Wzt1hcTrs0px7ZHW-qPzfTzkpsomAZLHxpg3XSZGohrlNxeWYvaVlZDkB6gCqw-QhZ9wyemMf_GJ8WBtrmrzYkA2uHJSHBwxgtYm2ENIXsodsscwcVxN3kFBYtvVAq33trli_cnzsu-vXjl9JtEeBQNPs0-O4YojpKn0Q2NsrtCzcC9RkXyqeDjD_fNgpsQR4BOL26xOvwzC0XZQNTGrWk3wjYo1evdvAhIYHK_f4p1lqHwfJTZzBeH_2bbF33sWWZWW4ZNKoFGhr68ymswAKLseR3artFSqN-O_VOFPDd2naBm52Al9UPXXvjMe_fCSknUy_hDlW97cnbwCsZEjIrP_ISlmPwZwBEuf5TE7CI4Svy21wpu9bZ8ROwttUnU7JoP1DsY1Wf_6QfgYZ5gM-QuUwAJtM9Z4DaK1V9YMyhrUEx55pTHlC5HkvciQ5l868U_9iBG0hlqGyxBwLIGgHETk4nIlbYb6d1Qqq_KGaunWdNAe6JE0xwTK_vrcfNgLk4yA7Ig7D_QQDyYTkaoilZHOk_-xLtasTiUfHn6wL6C-uTtj0F024Lo-2zGAHE_J02HwXLfnnsaQl_aHRxinB8u8ddn7-1guM1A7geGy2ogr21Fuzs8Xc-YXEJGKfhnhGDtzIbO9QaAx-EzKfbh-zUsX-Bk-3Mo_y0UHvIDeoDgfBtX0SYgMMk7iXzulpg86uMsNlNDDHHlpJZawsyE2k=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Thinking about method invocation**\\n\\nI’m considering how to invoke a method dynamically. It seems like I need the actual `Method#invoke` call to get this right. Maybe the active class should be a public bytecode that includes a public constructor. I think I could instantiate it using Java or Scala, making sure I understand the binary name. There’s a bit of complexity to navigate, but I’m curious about how it all ties together!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how the existing runtime compile process works; it only compiles without loading the compiled class, which might require a macro. I’m wondering if using a runtime source with a top-level val would help, but it seems that just compiling doesn't run it. Maybe I could use the Scala compiler with URLClassLoader for dynamic loading. I need to be careful with tests so that I'm not placing them in the same package, and I guess reflection might still be part of loading the generated class.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining test object structure**\\n\\nThe existing class file isn't active, so I should create private helpers 